idates Provides information on fundraising and campaign contributions for each candidate. Pew Forum on Religion & Public Life - 2012 Presidential Candidates Information about the 2012 presidential campaign and religion. The Tax Foundation - Election 2012: Presidential Candidate Tax Plan Comparison Provides interactive comparisons of each of the 2012 Republican candidates, both their general tax policy views and their positions on specific issues. Tax Policy Center - Tax Proposals by Republican Presidential Candidates Comparison of the provisions and distributional effects of the tax plans proposed by the major Republican presidential candidates. Includes a detailed grid. The Washington Post - Mad Money: Tracking TV campaign ads in the 2012 presidential campaign Watch campaign ads in the 2012 presidential campaign and track campaign ad spending by candidates and interest groups. Wikipedia - United States Presidential Election, 2012 Crowd-sourced encyclopedia article about the campaigns, candidates and elections. Last update: November 4, 2016 at 12:24:27 UTC Regional Science Shopping Society Sports All Languages Arts Business Computers Games Health Home News Recreation Reference "Regional ... 2012" search on: AOL - Ask - Bing - DuckDuckGo - Gigablast - Google - ixquick - Yahoo - Yandex - Yippy Copyright Â© 1998-2017 AOL Inc. Terms of Use Built by CMBuild